  "body": "Hi i got Debian 9 and latest geth.\r\nAnd i mount CIFS drive to /mnt/ethereum - and will use for blockchain.\r\n\r\nI have several geth node, all is fine work (except, time to time block is not high)\r\n\r\nAnd i got this error when node start:\r\n```\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum geth[21989]: WARN [07-16|17:11:01.105] Sanitizing cache to Go's GC limits       provided=2048 updated=1286\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum geth[21989]: INFO [07-16|17:11:01.106] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum geth[21989]: INFO [07-16|17:11:01.122] Starting peer-to-peer node               instance=Geth/v1.8.12-stable/linux-amd64/go1.10.3\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum geth[21989]: INFO [07-16|17:11:01.122] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/mnt/ethereum/geth/chaindata cache=964 handles=512\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum geth[21989]: Fatal: Error starting protocol stack: sync /mnt/ethereum/geth/chaindata: invalid argument\r\nJul 16 17:11:01 node-ethereum systemd[1]: geth.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=1/FAILURE\r\n```\r\n\r\ngeth create some files and fails.\r\n\r\n```\r\nroot@node-ethereum /mnt # tree ethereum\r\nethereum\r\n├── geth\r\n│   ├── chaindata\r\n│   │   ├── CURRENT\r\n│   │   ├── LOCK\r\n│   │   └── LOG\r\n│   ├── LOCK\r\n│   └── nodekey\r\n└── keystore\r\n```\r\nWhat additional run to check details ?\r\nCan geth work with SAMBA/CIFS/NFS disks ?\r\n\r\nThanks.",
