    "body": "In all honesty I wouldn't do that. Syncinc go-ethereum is already disk IO bound. If you're going to stream all the disk access through the network, I don't think you'll get a usable performance. That said, I would expect it to work, but it's not a use case we test for.\r\n\r\nYou'd probably need to also either disable the IPC endpoint, or move it to your local machine. Unix sockets need filesystem support, so that will most definitely not work on a remote datadir.",
